author: COMSOL
description: This example of a boxed loudspeaker lets you apply a nominal driving voltage and extract the resulting sound pressure level in the outside room as a function of the frequency. The electromagnetic properties of the driver are supplied from the Loudspeaker Driver model (available with the AC/DC Module). The example uses the Acousticâ€“Shell Interaction, Frequency Domain multiphysics interface and therefore requires the Structural Mechanics Module.
